                        "content": "Chemotherapy dosage is frequently based on total body surface area (BSA), so it is important for the nurse to perform which assessment before administering chemotherapy?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nTo ensure that the client receives optimal doses of chemotherapy, dosing is usually based on the total BSA, which requires a current accurate height and weight for BSA calculation (before each medication administration). Asking the client about current height and weight may lead to inaccuracies in determining a true BSA and dosage. Calculating body mass index and measuring abdominal girth will not provide the data needed.",
                        "id": "7d57e5762f0342a9bdbe31a30284048b",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4f685d5aa24e4a14b128ad20583fa0a4",
                                "content": "You can take aspirin as needed for headache."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "70998ed36945425d86c839d34ef1fb58",
                                "content": "You can drink beverages containing alcohol in moderate amounts each evening."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a08fc17a88b44ec5ba9352aa479c4202",
                                "content": "You need to consult with the primary health care provider (PHCP) before receiving immunizations."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "182125b50b7540f0a24c6ebc0087e66a",
                                "content": "It is fine to receive a flu vaccine at the local health fair without PHCP approval because the flu is so contagious."
                            }
