                        "content": "The nurse is monitoring a client for signs and symptoms related to superior vena cava syndrome. Which is an early sign of this oncological emergency?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nSuperior vena cava syndrome occurs when the superior vena cava is compressed or obstructed by tumor growth. Early signs and symptoms generally occur in the morning and include edema of the face, especially around the eyes, and client complaints of tightness of a shirt or blouse collar. As the compression worsens, the client experiences edema of the hands and arms. Cyanosis and mental status changes are late signs.",
                        "id": "9db0b67cc85a4b15ac422f8a18be1847",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ae6e69d520f54f419463c74b713c562d",
                                "content": "Clotting time 12 seconds"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "69366b4042004d89b9f0ec3f2249dce4",
                                "content": "Platelet count 50,000 mm3 (50 × 109/L)"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d44cc33bb9ba439681c18664fa58ff2b",
                                "content": "Ammonia level 28 mcg/dL (16.8 mcmol/L)"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b64dfe4d668740a7bca33f88ab379ed7",
                                "content": "White blood cell (WBC) count 4500 mm3 (4.5 × 109/L)"
                            }
                        ],
