                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse would be prepared to institute bleeding precautions in the client receiving antineoplastic medication if which result was reported from the laboratory?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPlatelets are the building blocks of blood clots. The normal platelet count is 150,000 to 400,000 mm3 (150 to 400 × 109/L). Bleeding precautions need to be instituted when the platelet count drops to a low level, as defined by agency policy. Bleeding precautions include avoiding all trauma, such as rectal temperatures or injections. The normal clotting time is 8 to 15 seconds. The normal ammonia value is 10 to 80 mcg/dL (6 to 47 mcmol/L). The normal WBC count is 5000 to 10,000 mm3 (5 to 10 × 109/L). When the WBC count drops, neutropenic precautions need to be implemented.",
                        "id": "c461aa017a554b7297452ba3b412a4e4",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "928da29bca354221818cae0aa3a6f3f8",
                                "content": "Anemia"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1efccacb76b04f10a69fca3696ec0c34",
                                "content": "Thrombocytopenia"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9652603b16564047992ed7c5bfe873dd",
                                "content": "Bone marrow suppression"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "076935c184924e7fb2835e51636255ac",
                                "content": "Low hemoglobin and hematocrit (H&H) counts"
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "928da29bca354221818cae0aa3a6f3f8",
                                    "content": "Anemia"
