                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nCancer is a neoplastic disorder that can involve all body systems. In cancer, cells lose their normal growth-controlling mechanism. Some signs and symptoms include sores that do not heal, a nagging cough or hoarseness, indigestion or difficulty swallowing, and a change in bowel or bladder habits. Areas of alopecia occur following cancer chemotherapy. Absence of menses is not a specific sign; however, abnormal occurrence of menses may be.",
